Text.Value: We came through the shadows together. That's not an experience one forgets.
A faith passed on by your father. He was ever loyal, even when the skies were darkest.
I can't thank you enough. For getting me out of that damned prison. And for giving me courage when I'd all but run out.
Your faith in this city is an inspiration.
It's the least I could do. You've proven a vital ally.
When the flames roared loudest, you pulled me to safety. Most would have let me burn - I won't forget it.
Not-so-encouraging words. If we're to crush the Absolute, we need to hold our heads high, and our weapons higher.
It's the least we could do. Your faith in this city should inspire us all.
I will travel to the Upper City, find what allies I can.
You won't fight the coming battle alone. As long as the city stands, I will stand with it. This is my promise.
I'm glad to see you free. You've proven a vital ally.
Good luck out there. You'll need it.
Speaking of inspiring - perhaps you'd be able to muster some allies of your own?
This is far enough - the way should be clear.
Don't be so quick with your gratitude, Counsellor. All we have done is send you back into the battle.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wryly amused - yes, we saved an ally, but she's going to need to work for it now. She might wish we'd left her where she was.

Text.Value: And reminded me why I fight it in the first place. Truly - thank you.
Yes. I have some connections in the Upper City - perhaps they'll heed our call.
Inspiring folk is what I do. Perhaps you could do the same - we need allies.

Synopsis: Florrick's dialog when you helped her leave the fortress.
